5/17/2018 DotRez API 101 - NextGen Booking Engine Home - Jetstar Wiki https://jetstar.jira.com/wiki/spaces/NGBE/pages/300155311/DotRez+API+101 1/9 / /NextGen Booking Engine HomePagesDotRez API DotRez API 101 Jem Del CarmenJan 12, 2018 Contents I. Introduction II. Getting Started III. Making your first request IV. Creating a booking I. Introduction 1. What is the dotRez API The dotRez API allows us to interact with the New Skies reservation system thru a "REST" interface.   Note: I put it in quotes because after trying it out, I realized that the dotRez API is not strictly REST because it is not stateless. This is a limitationbrought upon by New Skies remoting core. Nevertheless you can read the succeeding section for more information about REST . 2. What is REST? REST is acronym for REpresentational State Transfer. REST has it’s own 6 guiding constraints which must be satisfied if an interface needs to be referredas RESTful. These principles are listed below.Click here to expand...Guiding Principles of REST 1. Client–server – By separating the user interface concerns from the data storage concerns, we improve the portability of the user interface acrossmultiple platforms and improve scalability by simplifying the server components.2. Stateless – Each request from client to server must contain all of the information necessary to understand the request, and cannot take advantage ofany stored context on the server. Session state is therefore kept entirely on the client.3. Cacheable – Cache constraints require that the data within a response to a request be implicitly or explicitly labeled as cacheable or non-cacheable.If a response is cacheable, then a client cache is given the right to reuse that response data for later, equivalent requests.4. Uniform interface – By applying the software engineering principle of generality to the component interface, the overall system architecture issimplified and the visibility of interactions is improved. In order to obtain a uniform interface, multiple architectural constraints are needed to guidethe behavior of components. REST is defined by four interface constraints: identification of resources; manipulation of resources throughrepresentations; self-descriptive messages; and, hypermedia as the engine of application state.5. Layered system – The layered system style allows an architecture to be composed of hierarchical layers by constraining component behavior suchthat each component cannot “see” beyond the immediate layer with which they are interacting.6. Code on demand (optional) – REST allows client functionality to be extended by downloading and executing code in the form of applets or scripts.This simplifies clients by reducing the number of features required to be pre-implemented. visit https://restfulapi.net/ to read more about REST3. Why use REST?  Since REST is stateless, there are advantages in following the guiding principles. You can find a good discussion about ithere: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3105296/if-rest-applications-are-supposed-to-be-stateless-how-do-you-manage-sessions. Here's an informativequote from a reply in that discussion:Click here to expand..."By stateless it means that the server does not store any state about the client session on the server side. The client session is stored on the client. The server is stateless means that every server can service any client at any time, there is no session affinity or stickysessions. The relevant session information is stored on the client and passed to the server as needed. That does not preclude other services that the web server talks to from maintaining state about business objects such as shopping carts, just not about theclient's current application/session state. The client's application state should never be stored on the server, but passed around from the client to every place that needs it. That is where the ST in REST comes from, State Transfer. You transfer the state around instead of having the server store it. This is the only way to scale tomillions of concurrent users. If for no other reason than because millions of sessions is millions of sessions. The load of session management is amortized across all the clients, the clients store their session state and the servers can service many orders ofmagnitude or more clients in a stateless fashion. Even for a service that you think will only need in the 10's of thousands of concurrent users, you still should make your service stateless. Tens of thousandsis still tens of thousands and there will be time and space cost associated with it. Stateless is how the HTTP protocol and the web in general was designed to operate and is an overall simpler implementation and you have a single codepath instead of a bunch of server side logic to maintain a bunch of session state." II. Getting Started To start making API requests, you will need a tool such as CURL or Postman or ARC (Chrome extension) Postman - https://www.getpostman.com/  (RECOMMENDED)CURL - https://curl.haxx.se/download.html 5/17/2018 DotRez API 101 - NextGen Booking Engine Home - Jetstar Wiki https://jetstar.jira.com/wiki/spaces/NGBE/pages/300155311/DotRez+API+101 2/9 Advanced Rest Client (ARC) - Chrome extension : https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/advanced-rest-client/hgmloofddffdnphfgcellkdfbfbjeloo orWindows App: https://install.advancedrestclient.com/ III. Making your first request First of all you will need a subscription key, which you can request in https://sandboxnavitaire.portal.azure-api.net/ To start making requests, you must get an authorization token from the API first. Make sure all request headers are correct. Sample Request:

HeadersContent-Type: application/json Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key: {subscription key} Sample Response: Body{ "data": {"token": "{token}", "idleTimeoutInMinutes": 15 }, "metadata": { "documentation_url":"http://developer.navitaire.com/documentation/dotrezapi/nsktoken" }} You will need to copy the generated token, and use it for succeeding requests For all succeeding requests, the header MUST contain: HeadersContent-Type: application/json authorization: {token} EDIT: You can also connect to the Jetstar dotRez API TEST environment using this base URL :  https://170.248.100.198/api/nsk/ You don't need a subscription key for this one, but you have to be connected to the Jetstar VPN network. EDIT: You can run your own dotRez API on your local machine, and set it as your endpoint URL. IV. Creating a booking 1. In the standard booking flow, we start with flight search. This means we need to check the availability of flights. 5/17/2018 Extending DotRez API - Custom Controllers, Proxies, and ServiceModels - NextGen Booking Engine Home - Jetstar Wiki https://jetstar.jira.com/wiki/spaces/NGBE/pages/300155332/Extending+DotRez+API+-+Custom+Controllers+Proxies+and+ServiceModels 1/4 / /NextGen Booking Engine HomePages DotRez API Extending DotRez API - Custom Controllers, Proxies, and ServiceModels Jem Del Carmen Last modified Jan 16, 2018 Introduction To prove that we can extend DotRez API, we are going to implement custom code to allow us to get the stateless fee object, using a remoting service call "GetFeeDeep". Custom Proxy First step is to create the custom proxy. This will perform the remote service call to "GetFeeDeep". This is the code for IFinanceProxy and FinanceProxy: Click here to expand... using System; using Navitaire.DotRez.Core.Exceptions; using Navitaire.DotRez.Core.Services; using Navitaire.NewSkies.RemotingServices.Interfaces.FinanceManager; using Navitaire.DotRez.Core.Utilities; using Navitaire.DotRez.Nsk.Common.Enumerations; using Navitaire.DotRez.Nsk.Common.Extensions; using Navitaire.NewSkies.Common; using Navitaire.NewSkies.Common.Enumerations; using Navitaire.NewSkies.Messages.Finance.Fee; namespace Api_Custom_Endpoints.Proxies public interface IFinanceProxy { Fee GetFeeDeep(string feeCode); } public class FinanceProxy : IFinanceProxy { private Navitaire.DotRez.Core.Remoting.Services.IRemoteService<IFinanceM private IServiceInvoker ServiceInvoker { get; } private ISessionService SessionService { get; } 5/17/2018 Extending DotRez API - Custom Controllers, Proxies, and ServiceModels - NextGen Booking Engine Home - Jetstar Wiki https://jetstar.jira.com/wiki/spaces/NGBE/pages/300155332/Extending+DotRez+API+-+Custom+Controllers+Proxies+and+ServiceModels 2/4 public FinanceProxy(ISessionService sessionService, IServiceInvoker serv { SessionService = sessionService; FinanceManager = financeManager ?? throw new ArgumentNullException(n ServiceInvoker = serviceInvoker; } public Fee GetFeeDeep(string feeCode) { var sessionToken = GetSessionContext(SessionService); var request = feeCode; var response = ServiceInvoker.Call("FinanceManager.FindCurrencyConve () => FinanceManager.Get().GetFeeDeep(sessionToken, request) ); return response; } public static SessionContext GetSessionContext(ISessionService service) { if (service == null) { throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(service)); } var nskContext = service.GetNskContext(); var sessionContext = service.GetContext(); var context = new SessionContext { SystemType = EnumerationUtility.Convert<SystemName, SystemType>( ChannelType = EnumerationUtility.Convert<Navitaire.DotRez.Nsk.Co SessionControl = SessionControl.First, SessionID = NonNullableValue.Convert(nskContext.ServerContext?.I ClientName = NonNullableValue.Convert(sessionContext?.Applicatio SecureToken = NonNullableValue.Convert(nskContext.ServerContext? }; var convertedContext = context; if (convertedContext == null) { throw new UnknownSessionException(); } return convertedContext; } } } 5/17/2018 Extending DotRez API - Custom Controllers, Proxies, and ServiceModels - NextGen Booking Engine Home - Jetstar Wiki https://jetstar.jira.com/wiki/spaces/NGBE/pages/300155332/Extending+DotRez+API+-+Custom+Controllers+Proxies+and+ServiceModels 3/4 Custom ServiceModel Next is the ServiceModel which will call the Proxy: Click here to expand... Register the Proxy and the ServiceModel Inside StartupModule.cs  register the custom proxy and serviceModel in the ConfigureServices() method: Click here to expand... using Api_Custom_Endpoints.Interfaces; using Api_Custom_Endpoints.Proxies; using Navitaire.NewSkies.Messages.Finance.Fee; namespace Api_Custom_Endpoints.Interfaces public interface IFinanceServiceModel { /// <summary> ///     Retrieves all fees. /// </summary> /// <returns>Fees</returns> Fee GetFeeDeep(string feeCode); } } namespace Api_Custom_Endpoints.ServiceModels public class FinanceServiceModel : IFinanceServiceModel { public IFinanceProxy FinanceProxy { get; } public FinanceServiceModel(IFinanceProxy financeProxy) { FinanceProxy = financeProxy; } public Fee GetFeeDeep(string feeCode) { return FinanceProxy.GetFeeDeep(feeCode); } } } 5/17/2018 Extending DotRez API - Custom Controllers, Proxies, and ServiceModels - NextGen Booking Engine Home - Jetstar Wiki https://jetstar.jira.com/wiki/spaces/NGBE/pages/300155332/Extending+DotRez+API+-+Custom+Controllers+Proxies+and+ServiceModels 4/4 Custom Endpoint (Controller) Lastly, define this endpoint in your custom controller: Click here to expand... When we call the endpoint GET /jetstar/getfeedeep we can get the resulting fee. (you can see the sample response here: [DotRez API] Fees) Like Be the first to like this services.AddSingleton<IFinanceProxy, FinanceProxy>(); services.AddSingleton<IFinanceServiceModel, FinanceServiceModel>(); public IActionResult GetFeeDeep([FromQuery]string feeCode) var result = FinanceServiceModel.GetFeeDeep(feeCode); return ResponseService.Value(this, result); }  No labels

The simple search request covers the common search criteria and lets default settings (LowFareAvailabilitySettings) configure the rest. /api/nsk/v3/availability/search/simple query availiabilitySimplev3Searches for availability with the simple search request. The simple search request covers the common search criteria and lets default settings (AvailabilitySettings) configure the rest.

availability with the full low fare search request. This request allows for total control over the configuration. If a property is not set, the default settings (LowFareAvailabilitySettings) are used in its place.

the full availability search request. This request allows for total control over the configuration. If a property is not set, the default settings (AvailabilitySettings) are used in its place. Notes: Specifying the passenger count on the request does not affect the availability result. We will need to check the availableCount field under the fare to make sure there are enough fares to book the passengers. 5/17/2018 [DotRez API] Availability and Fares - NextGen Booking Engine Home - Jetstar Wiki https://jetstar.jira.com/wiki/spaces/NGBE/pages/301563905/DotRez+API+Availability+and+Fares 2/4 Although this endpoint behaves like a GET, a POST implementation removes the limitations resulting from URL length issues. the fareAvailabilityKey is not unique in the sense that it is only unique within its journey: the fareAvailable node contains the detailed information for each fare (based on fareAvailabilityKey): 5/17/2018 [DotRez API] Availability and Fares - NextGen Booking Engine Home - Jetstar Wiki https://jetstar.jira.com/wiki/spaces/NGBE/pages/301563905/DotRez+API+Availability+and+Fares 3/4 Low fare availability (/lowfare/simple) Notes: Lowfare search returns the lowest fare for each date market, as well as the lowest fare for each flight available on each date market. You can specify daysToLeft and daysToRight which is the number of days before and after to include in the search. A 7-day search would have a value of 3 for both. request: response: (each date market contains multiple lowfare entries which is the lowest fare for that flight) 5/17/2018 [DotRez API] Availability and Fares - NextGen Booking Engine Home - Jetstar Wiki https://jetstar.jira.com/wiki/spaces/NGBE/pages/301563905/DotRez+API+Availability+and+Fares 4/4 Fare Rules dotRez API endpoint GraphQL method Notes

Note: A possible workaround is to create a custom proxy and/or serviceModel to achieve this Getting Fees Typically you can get fees after flights are selected.
